Hi there,
In our project we use single model with 2 roles like in this snippet:

```python
    class Address(Model):
        class Options:
            roles = {
                'full': whitelist('street', 'zipcode'),
                'short': whitelist('street')
            }
        zipcode = StringType(required=True)
        street = StringType(required=True)

    class User(Model):
        class Options:
            roles = {
                'full': whitelist('name', 'age', 'address'),
                'short': whitelist('name', 'address')
            }
        name = StringType(required=True)
        age = IntType(required=True)
        address = ModelType(Address, required=True)
```
And I can not understand why there is no validation using some role. 
When role=short I think that validation should be done without exceptions for such json: 
```javascript
 {
        'name': 'Bob',
        'address': {
            'street': 'somewhere in the world'
        }
}
```
Can somebody point me in the right direction If there are any problems with PR

~~Super WIP here! Just posting so everyone knows which segment I'm touching.~~

Taking a stab at a new interface for the `<ExecuteResult />`, `<DisplayData />`, and `<RichMedia />`. This starts with _only_ `<RichMedia />` for the moment.

Demo: https://declarative-trial.nteract.io/#!/RichMedia

Here's a snippet of the new interface:

```jsx
// Declare a component for rendering plaintext
const Plain = props => <pre>{props.data}</pre>;
Plain.defaultProps = {
  mediaType: "text/plain"
};

// Declare a component for rendering HTML
const HTML = props => <div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: props.data }} />;
HTML.defaultProps = {
  mediaType: "text/html"
};

<RichMedia
  data={{
    "text/plain": "plain was richer",
    "text/html": "<b>HTML is so much richer</b>"
  }}
>
  <HTML />
  <Plain />
</RichMedia>
```


Miscellaneous TODO as I come across them, so I don't forget:

* ~~`@nteract/presentational-components` now depends on `@nteract/records` solely for types -- need to figure out if this should be a hard dependency~~ included a simple type for now...

For later:

* Much of the styling of `<Outputs />` should only be affecting the html and markdown types. Right now it's this global grab bag of things.
* ~~We need to make it super easy to special case handling of the data explorer, to give it control over height~~ Hopefully this is good now with our declarative `<RichMedia>` component
* ~~How we do transforms should become simpler _somehow_~~ Possibly solved here
* ~~`onMetadataChange` should be passed in here~~ Hey I think we can at least do this with the Data Explorer with this setup.

The batch API accepts payloads of the form

```
{
    "time": "<time>",
    "samplerate": 22,
    "data": {...}
}
```

not

```
{
    "timestamp": "<time>",
    "samplerate": 22,
    "data": {...}
}
```

Doh!

Test plan: run test script and verify results in UI; new unit test

